lon was listed as one of americas top five cosmetic houses expanding its capabilities the company bought graef  schmidt a cutlery manufacturer seized by the government in  because of german business ties this acquisition made it possible for revlon to produce its own manicure and pedicure instruments instead of buying them from outside supply sources in november  revlon went public the ipo price was  per share but it reached  per share within  weeks in the s revson segmented revlon inc into different divisions each focusing on a different market he borrowed this strategy from general motors each division had its own target customer revlon the largest and most popularpriced brand princess marcella borghese upscaleinternational ultima ii premium natural wonder juniors moon drops dry skin etherea hypoallergenic in  revlon acquired knomark a shoepolish company and sold its shoepolish line esquire shoe polish in  other acquisitions such as tydbol the maker of toilet cleansers and a  percent interest in the schick electric shaver company were soon discarded evan picone a womens sportswear manufacturer which came with a price tag of  million in  was sold back to one of the original partners four years later for  million however the  acquisition of us vitamin and pharmaceutical corporation made revlon a leader in diabetes drugs the company began to market its products overseas at the end of the s by  when revlon debuted in japan there were subsidiaries in france italy argentina mexico and asia revlons entrance into the japanese market was typical of its international sales strategy instead of adapting its ads and using japanese models revlon chose to use its basic us advertising and models japanese women loved the american look and the sales for  came to almost  million in  revlon introduced eterna the first cosmetic cream with an estrogen precursor called progenitin pregenolone acetate as well as introducing the worlds first american fashion designer fragrance norman norell later revlon launched braggi and pub for men and a line of wig maintenance products called wig wonder in  revlon acquired the mitchum line of deodorants in  flex shampoo and conditioner was introduced in  revlon introduced charlie geared to the under market charlie model shelley hack in ralph lauren clothes personified the independent woman of the s this was the first perfume ad to feature a woman wearing pants charlie raised revlons net sales figures to  million for  and almost  million the following year shelley hack appeared on oprah in  to talk about the power of these charlie print and commercial ads their followup fragrance jontue became the number two best seller in  model lauren hutton signed an exclusive modeling contract agreeing to pose for revlons ultima line for  for two years she was featured on the cover of newsweek for this groundbreaking cosmetics contract additionally famed photographer richard avedon was signed on as the exclusive photographer for the brand  another cosmetics industry first michel begerac control edit in  charles revson died michel bergerac who revson had hired as president of the company continued to expand the company holdings revlon acquired coburn optical industries an oklahomabased manufacturer of ophthalmic and optical processing equipment and supplies barneshind the largest us marketer of hard contact lens solutions was bought in  and strengthened revlons share of the eyecare market revlon purchased armour pharmaceutical company a division of armour and company from the greyhound corporation in  other acquisitions included the lewishowe company makers of tums antacid in  these healthcare operations helped sales figures to pass the  billion mark in  bringing total sales to  billion in  in the mids revlon lost ground to estée lauder estee lauder spent millions of dollars on numerous magazine ads featuring czech supermodel paulina porizkova shot by famed chicago fashion photographer victor skrebneski revlons share dropped from  percent to  percent of department store cosmetics sales sales at the drugstore also declined as revlon lost shares to noxells cover girl brand revlon compensated with more acquisitions max factor ellen betrix charles of the ritz germaine monteil almay fermodyl lancaster aziza and halston the  acquisition of carlos colomer a spanish professional beauty supply distributor brought fermodyl and roux and helped introduce revlon to the world of ethnic care creme of nature realistic lovely color and milk and honey in  the company attempted an unsuccessful hostile takeover of gillette in  revlon became one of the first companies to replace animal tests with alternative safety testing methods revlon counter in new zealand department store farmers ronald perelman control presentedit on november   at a price of  per share totaling  billion revlon was sold to pantry pride later renamed to revlon group inc a subsidiary of ronald perelmans macandrews  forbes the buyout—engineered with the help of junk bond king michael p milken—saddled revlon with a huge  billion debt load which became an albatross around the companys neck for years to come pantry pride inc offered to buy any or all of revlons  million outstanding shares for  a share when its street price stood at  a share initially rejected he repeatedly raised his offer until it reached  a share while fighting revlons management every step of the way forstmann little  company swooped in at  a share a brief public bidding war ensued and perelman triumphed with an offer of  a share perelman paid  billion to revlons shareholders but he also paid  million of other costs associated with the purchase perelman had revlon sell four divisions two for  billion the vision care division for  million and the national health laboratories division which became a publicly owned corporation in  additional makeup lines were purchased for revlon max factor in  and betrix in  later sold to procter  gamble in  also in  revlon sold the clean  clear brand to johnson  johnson in march  revlon acquired mirage cosmetics makers of sinful colors nail products in  peta removed revlon and other highprofile cosmetic brands from its list of companies who do not test their products on animals after the organization learned they were paying chinese laboratories to test their cosmetics on rabbits and other animals in august  revlon consumer products corp bought the colomer group from cvc capital partners a private equity firm for  million after suffering business loss in  and  at the end of  revlon announced that it will exit the chinese market which employs  people the business in china accounted for just  percent portion of net sales of revlons international operations on november   revlon named lorenzo delpani as president and ceo  on september   revlons board of directors elected roberto simon as executive vice president and chief financial officer effective as of sept  advertisingedit tram with revlon advertising in hong kong june  up until the s revlons magazine ads were drawn by hand and mostly in black and white beginning in  revlon began launching fullcolor photographic advertisements in major magazines and stores across the country revlon introduced matching nail polish and lipsticks with exotic and unique names these ads were taken by the top fashion photographers of the day including richard avedon cecil beaton and john rawlings some of these ads were for paint the town pink and s fatal apple with dorian leigh in  revlon introduced bachelors carnation and in  sweet talk in  revlon introduced a red lipstick and nail enamel called wheres the fire revlon used the word fire again later in their fire and ice ads one of the worlds first supermodels dorian leigh starred in some of revlons most memorable advertisements of all time in  dorian was covered in purple flowers and wrapped in a pale purple sheet for ultra violet in  dorian appeared in fashion plate in  at the age of  she appeared in cherries in the snow later that year she appeared in the legendary fire and ice ad shot by richard avedon originally dorian appeared in a tight silverbeaded dress with an enormous red wrap her black hair had a silver swirl in it and she had her hands with long red nails positioned in front of her breasts charles revson rejected avedons original ad as too sexual they reshot the ad this time with her open hand in front of one hip the other in front of her cheek the advertisement became madison avenue legend because of the fullpage quiz next to the sensual ad almost  years later in november  revlon recreated s fire and ice magazine ad this time with actress jessica biel with this ad revlon announced they were issuing a limited edition fire and ice lipstick and nail color calling this campaign lips and tips dorian leighs yearsyounger redheaded sister suzy parker also shot numerous revlon magazine ads in the s charles revson who wanted to marry dorian at some point despised suzy and vice versa at one point he refused to hire her anymore because suzy complained about the peanut paycheck she received from revlon richard avedon however after photographing other models for a particular revlon ad would call in suzy last minute sometimes late at night to do retakes with him this happened with stormy pink an ad suzy shot very late at night with a wild white horse in the ocean avedon would then tell revson that it was not suzy in the ad but a model named bubbles or another madeup name in  revlon became the first american cosmetics company to feature an african american model naomi sims in their advertising revlon was also noted for featuring models of a wide age range in the s including then yearold milla jovovich and then yearold audrey hepburn despite the successful campaigns of the s and s featuring models in particular cindy crawford revlon decided to drop fashion models and focus on movie stars among them kate bosworth jaime king halle berry susan sarandon melanie griffith julianne moore eva mendes jessica alba jennifer connelly beau garrett jessica biel olivia wilde emma stone and bond girls in  australian supermodel elle macpherson became a new spokesmodel for the company american actress jessica biel is the newest woman to model for the brand first shown in advertisements in january  main article list of revlon spokesmodels in  celebrity makeup artist gucci westman was hired as revlons global artistic director representing the company at runway shows and brand events and designing collections philanthropyedit becky gulsvig at revlon runwalk for cancer revlon is a corporate sponsor of several charity projects the largest of these is the revlon run walk a run and walk event held in new york and los angeles to raise money and awareness for breast and ovarian cancer revlon also supports other cancer charities such as look good feel better and the national breast cancer coalition and operates a mobile mammography clinic in and around oxford north carolina where the companys primary manufacturing operations are located in  revlon supported the development of a breast center at the university of california los angeles renamed revlonucla breast center the center is a wellknown institute for treatment and research of breast cancer and other breast diseases and disorders a revlon lip gloss shade whose proceeds support revlons cancer charities was also created in  in september  revlon with global artistic director gucci westman and spokesmodel halle berry hosted an event at fashions night out in new york city to raise funds for the jenesse center a los angeles organization for domestic violence victims revlon also hosted luncheons and various other events to benefit the center and partnered with online retailer drugstorecom to donate portions of lipstick sales to the organization see alsoedit list of revlon spokesmodels referencesedit  a b c financial statements for revlon  morningstar morningstarcom  retrieved    a b financials for revlon google finance  retrieve